66.2	Deus_Ex	Deus Ex	Deus Ex (abbreviated DX and -É™s ) is an action role-playing game developed by Ion Storm Inc. and published by Eidos Interactive in 2000, which combines gameplay elements of first-person shooters with those of role-playing video games. The game received universal critical and industry acclaim, including being named "Best PC Game of All Time" in PC Gamer's Top 100 PC Games and in a poll carried out by UK gaming magazine PC Zone. It was a frequent candidate for and winner of Game of the Year awards, drawing praise for its pioneering designs in player choice and multiple narrative paths. It has sold more than 1 million copies, as of April 23, 2009.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/42/Dxcover.jpg/250px-Dxcover.jpg
